John B. Sherman of Texas has been nominated to be the Chief Information Officer of the Intelligence Community, Office of the Director of National Intelligence. He currently serves as the Deputy Director of CIA's Open Source Enterprise and has been involved in incorporating open source intelligence into the IC Information Technology Enterprise. Sherman has over 20 years of experience in the intelligence community, starting as a satellite imagery analyst and manager and serving as a duty officer in the White House Situation Room. He has held senior executive positions at the National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency (NGA) and served as the Principal Deputy National Intelligence Officer for Military Issues on the National Intelligence Council. Sherman has received several awards for his service, including the Meritorious Presidential Rank Award, CIA Intelligence Medal of Merit, and NGA Meritorious Civilian Service Medal. Prior to his career in the intelligence community, he served as a U.S. Army Air Defense officer. Sherman holds a B.A. in History from Texas A&M University and an M.P.A. from the University of Houston.